_json.description: Fibromyalgia Eye Problems :            Fibromyalgia, a chronic, debilitating, autoimmune syndrome causing severe pain in the muscles and tissues as well as fatigue in over 6 million people in the U.S. alone, often causes various other problems, including eye and vision problems. Fibromyalgia affects the nervous system, and therefore, can impact eyesight. It can cause the eyes to become sensitive to both light and touch, and can induce dry eyes, blurred vision, and even blindness.
